President Joseph R. Biden Jr. has delegated authority to the Secretary of State to direct the drawdown of up to $775 million in defense articles and services, as well as military education and training, to provide assistance to Ukraine. This delegation is made under section 506(a)(1) of the Foreign Assistance Act of 1961. The Secretary of State will also be responsible for making the necessary determinations required under this section to direct the drawdown. The memorandum authorizing this delegation will be published in the Federal Register.